Time to remind everyone, written by C.J. Cherryh
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Chanur_novels
>The Pride of Chanur
>Chanur's Venture
>The Kiff Strike Back
>Chanur's Homecoming
>Chanur's Legacy

Stuck on a spaceship full of space cats. Very nearly only the females are sane and stable enough to handle off-planet travel. Some find humans weirdly attractive. Space cats form prides around a single male, if he's strong enough (the novels explore strength as spirit & soul, apart from traditional physical).

Unfortunately, very PG-13 rating, so no space cat sexy (other than implied). But, still, a rollicking good series written by one of the best science fiction writers in the last 100 years. This one she wrote for fun rather than depth, but still lots of sci fi head candy sprinkled throughout. Also unfortunately, there could have been half a dozen more novels, but she went on to new projects and this is all we have.

Strong recommend for guilty pleasure & fun. Space cats go shirtless, always & everywhere, and take enormous pride in the fastidious appearance of their glorious manes. Very Not Gay.
